  - Sacrifice-Death=Illusion=The Consummation of Desire
By: Hermes
Commentary: (The thought world is) the world of archetypal Ideas. The text is
  an English rendering of a Latin translation from an Arabic manuscript. The
  editor offers r à votjrà eîSij, Ta Svrwç ovra. as a guess for the Greek
  original.
---
Know that all the shapes and images which you see with your bodily eyes in the
world of things that come to be and cease to be are mere semblances and copies
of the forms which have real existence in the thought-world, those forms which
are eternal and will never cease to be.
